# Telegram mirror for agent review

The bot logs every Telegram message (in + out) to `telegram_mirror.jsonl` on the server.

## Pull recent messages (no user copy-paste)

```bash
cd /Users/manikandan.palanisamy/Downloads/bnf-bot-main
python3 scripts/pull_telegram_mirror.py --limit 50
```

Then read: `logs/telegram_mirror.jsonl`

## Server path

`~/bnf-bot/telegram_mirror.jsonl` on `BOT_SERVER_SSH` from `.env` (default `root@64.227.177.10`).

## When to pull

- User shares or asks about morning brief, sim report, /groww, errors
- User says "check telegram" or "what did the bot send"
- Debugging training phase / sim count without asking user to paste

## SSH one-liner (if scp fails)

```bash
ssh root@SERVER 'tail -40 ~/bnf-bot/telegram_mirror.jsonl'
```

Do not commit `telegram_mirror.jsonl` or paste bot tokens from the log.
